---
description: Rules for creating a new feature (ui/domain/data/data-network modules) for KMP + Decompose + MVI
alwaysApply: false
---

## Scope
This rules file is intended **exclusively** for use by the agent `.cursor/agents/feature-module-generator.md` during new feature scaffolding.

## Feature structure

- **One feature = several modules**:
  - `features/<featureName>/<featureName>-ui`
  - `features/<featureName>/<featureName>-domain`
  - `features/<featureName>/<featureName>-data`
  - `features/<featureName>/<featureName>-data-network`
  - (optional) use shared module `common/persistence/persistence-database` instead of a dedicated `data-storage` module
- **Optional ui-components module**:
  - Use **only if** shared UI components are hard to move to `common/uikit`.
  - Name: `features/<featureName>/<featureName>-ui-components`.

## Package naming

- **Base prefix**: `io.pylyp.<featureName>.<layer>`
  - UI: `io.pylyp.<featureName>.ui`
  - Domain: `io.pylyp.<featureName>.domain`
  - Data: `io.pylyp.<featureName>.data`
  - Data-network: `io.pylyp.<featureName>.data.network`
- **Namespace in Gradle**:
  - In `androidLibrary { namespace = "io.pylyp.<featureName>.<layer>" }` use the same `<featureName>` and `<layer>` pattern as in the package names above.

## Module relationships

- **In-feature dependencies**:
  - `*-ui` depends on:
    - its own `*-domain`
    - `common/core-ui`
  - `*-domain` depends on:
    - `common/core-domain`
  - `*-data` depends on:
    - its own `*-domain`
    - `*-data-network`
    - `common/core-di`
    - `common/persistence/persistence-database` (for Room/DB)
  - `*-data-network` depends on:
    - `common/core-di`
    - `common/core-network`
- **Forbidden**:
  - `*-ui` must not depend directly on `*-data` or `*-data-network`.
  - Domain must not depend on UI or Data/Network.

## Gradle and plugins

- **Base plugins for feature modules**:
  - All feature modules use:
    - `alias(libs.plugins.app.kotlinMultiplatform)`
- **Additional plugins per layer**:
  - UI module:
    - `alias(libs.plugins.app.kotlinMultiplatform)`
    - `alias(libs.plugins.app.composeMultiplatform)`
    - (if needed) `alias(libs.plugins.kotlinxSerialization)`
  - Domain module:
    - **only** `alias(libs.plugins.app.kotlinMultiplatform)`
  - Data / Data-network modules:
    - `alias(libs.plugins.app.kotlinMultiplatform)`
    - `alias(libs.plugins.kotlinxSerialization)` if there are DTOs/network
- **Do NOT use Compose plugin where it is not needed**:
  - It is forbidden to apply `alias(libs.plugins.app.composeMultiplatform)` in:
    - `*-domain`
    - `*-data`
    - `*-data-network`
    - any data/storage/persistence modules.

## Creating a new feature (checklist)

- **1. Create feature directory**:
  - `features/<featureName>/`
- **2. Create modules**:
  - `features/<featureName>/<featureName>-ui`
  - `features/<featureName>/<featureName>-domain`
  - `features/<featureName>/<featureName>-data`
  - `features/<featureName>/<featureName>-data-network`
- **3. Configure Gradle for each module**:
  - Use the plugin set and namespace rules described in this document.
  - Add only the dependencies required for the given layer.
- **4. Configure DI (Koin) for the feature**:
  - Declare Koin modules for:
    - data / data-network repositories
    - domain use cases
    - ui components / Decompose components
  - Keep registrations split per layer, in separate files.

## Special cases: ui-components

- **When it is allowed to create `*-ui-components`**:
  - When multiple screens/features of the same domain share complex UI components that do not belong in the global `uikit`.
  - Example: domain-specific widgets reused across multiple screens of the same feature.
- **Requirements for `*-ui-components`**:
  - Must not contain business logic.
  - Must not depend directly on Data/Domain, only on:
    - `common/core-ui`
    - possible other UI modules of the same feature.

